221
00:13:43,400 --> 00:13:46,552
Have you ever wondered
how the pop charts are compiled?

222
00:13:46,600 --> 00:13:48,876
Well, every time you buy a record,

223
00:13:48,920 --> 00:13:51,435
the record shop owner
immediately notifies

224
00:13:51,480 --> 00:13:53,676
the people who put
the charts together,

225
00:13:53,720 --> 00:13:55,951
the Royal Pop and Rock Association,

226
00:13:56,000 --> 00:13:58,310
using a system of pneumatic tubes.

227
00:14:00,120 --> 00:14:03,750
Once it arrives at ROPRA,
the sale is logged

228
00:14:03,800 --> 00:14:07,680
and that information
is used to calculate the positions

229
00:14:07,720 --> 00:14:09,552
of the songs in the charts.

230
00:14:09,600 --> 00:14:13,150
However, the pneumatic tubes
themselves are pretty old

231
00:14:13,200 --> 00:14:15,157
and often get clogged up.

232
00:14:15,200 --> 00:14:19,672
Worse still, because so many other
businesses use this tube system,

233
00:14:19,720 --> 00:14:22,360
the information
sometimes gets mixed up,

234
00:14:22,400 --> 00:14:25,552
which can lead to
discrepancies in the charts.

235
00:14:25,600 --> 00:14:27,557
We all remember last year's fiasco

236
00:14:27,600 --> 00:14:32,072
when the Post Office tower spent
six consecutive weeks at No.1.

237
00:14:33,640 --> 00:14:37,634
So in the words of Elvis Presley,
"Something had to be done."

238
00:14:37,680 --> 00:14:41,071
And here at ROPRA's headquarters,
in London's West End,

239
00:14:41,120 --> 00:14:43,112
something is being done.

240
00:14:47,760 --> 00:14:51,151
Sir Alan Rees
is the chairman of ROPRA.

241
00:14:51,200 --> 00:14:53,192
- (Knocking)
- Go out.

242
00:14:54,120 --> 00:14:56,680
Sir Alan, what is being done?

243
00:14:56,720 --> 00:14:59,713
Well, we're phasing out
the whole pneumatic tube system

244
00:14:59,760 --> 00:15:01,752
because it's clearly not working.

245
00:15:01,800 --> 00:15:04,156
As well as
the Post Office tower business,

246
00:15:04,200 --> 00:15:06,795
we've had everything from a coat
hangar in the Top 10

247
00:15:06,840 --> 00:15:11,039
to a motor insurance policy
popping in and out of the charts

248
00:15:11,080 --> 00:15:12,753
and driving everybody mad.

